Kim Jong Il Sends Message of Greetings to Putin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent a message of greetings to Russian President V.V. Putin on Tuesday, on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Korea's liberation.
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I extend felicitations to you and, through you, to the Russian people on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wish you success in your responsible work for the socio-economic development of the country, expressing the belief that the DPRK-Russia relations will expand and develop in different fields in the spirit of the documents agreed upon between the two sides.

Greetings to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a message of greetings from Russian President Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin on Monday on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Korea's liberation.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Please accept my sincere felicitations to you on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Korea's liberation, the national holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people achieved their freedom and independence through a heroic struggle against the colonial oppression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Soldiers of the Soviet Army made a great contribution to the liberation of Korea in August 1945. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This stern trial helped strengthen the solid and long tradition of friendship and good-neighborliness between the peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the relations between Russia and the DPRK are making constructive progress.
 It is my belief that developing the bilateral cooperation and carrying out long-term economic plans are conducive to preserving peace and security and achieving stability on the Korean Peninsula and in the rest of Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Esteemed Your Excellency Chairman, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Please accept my best wishes for your good health and new success in the implementation of the important tasks facing the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sincerely Yours.

"Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" Vol.64 Brought Out 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- "Complete Collection of   Kim Il Sung's Works" Vol. 64, a library of the great Juche idea, was brought out by the Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House.
 It contains 38 works including speeches, talks and conclusions President Kim Il Sung made from September to October, Juche 66 (1977). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That period urged the Korean people to deepen the three revolutions, ideological, technical and cultural, advance socialist construction to a new higher stage on the basis of the achievements in carrying out the 6-year plan. The period also urged the world revolutionary people to wage a dynamic struggle against all the dominationist forces.
 The works make a comprehensive compilation of outstanding ideas and theories and policies on firmly building up the driving force of the Korean revolution to meet the new requirements of the revolution, on making the man-centered Korean-style socialist system invincible by strengthening the might of the country in every way and on dynamically performing the Korean revolution and waging dynamic struggle for independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President in his work "Theses on Socialist Education" newly put forward the original and scientific idea on the basic principle of socialist pedagogy and flawlessly clarified the principle, contents and methods of socialist education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his works including "On Giving Definite Priority to the Mining Industry over the Manufacturing Industry" and "Let's Do Farming Well Next Year" elucidated tasks and ways to develop the national economy and push ahead with economic construction as required by the socialist economic law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his works "A Letter of Good Wishes to the Eleventh Congress of Chongryon" and "On Strengthening the Chapters and Branches of Chongryon and Working Efficiently with the People from All Walks of Life" clarified the tasks which would serve as guidelines in the activities of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Other works deal with the principled issues arising in accomplishing the cause of independence against imperialism including ways of driving the U.S. forces out of south Korea and achieving the democratization of society and the issue of forming the united front in the struggle against imperialism.

Withdrawal of NSL Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly called a press conference in Seoul on August 10 to press for the lift of the "National Security Law" and revocation of listing Hanchongryon as an "enemy-benefiting organization".
 Speakers at the press conference disclosed the fact that many students have been arrested and wanted by police since Hanchongryon was listed as an "enemy-benefiting organization" on the strength of the law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the students will conduct a more vigorous struggle to put an end to the inhuman NSL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the press conference, the participants thrust into Chongwadae a message pressing for the withdrawal of NSL and a stop to the listing of Hanchongryon as "an enemy-benefiting organization."

Friendly Gathering Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- The DPRK-India Friendship Association hosted a friendly meeting with the staff members of the Indian embassy at DPRK-India Friendship Pyongyang Wasan Middle School on August 14.
 Present on invitation were N. T. Khankhup, Indian ambassador to the DPRK, and staff members of the Indian embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and vice-chairman of the DPRK-India Friendship Association, officials concerned and teachers and students of the school.
 Being briefed on the instructional and educational work of the school, the participants went round the educational facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They enjoyed an art performance given by the students of the school and deepened their friendly feelings, talking about the need to boost cultural exchange between the DPRK and India. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members of the Indian embassy donated educational equipment to the school that day.

Posters of 2nd International Martial Arts Games Published
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- Posters of the 2nd International Martial Arts Games to be held in Pyongyang were published.
 The posters reflect the desire of the Korean people and other peoples of the world to build an independent and peaceful new world in the idea of independence, peace and friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are a poster bearing letters "Welcome" and a mark of the games and depicting a bouquet warmly welcoming men of martial arts from different countries, a poster depicting the kicking technique of orthodox martial arts of the Korean nation Taekwon-do and Korean wrestling game and a poster showing technical movements of national martial arts widely spread in different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The posters have been pasted up in different parts of Pyongyang to add to the atmosphere of the 2nd International Martial Arts Games.

RS on Forcing Japan to Pay for Its Crimes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- The Korean people will certainly force Japan, the sworn enemy, to pay for its crimes, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today. 
 The Japanese government is driving the DPRK-Japan hostile relations up to the line of explosion by escalating its hostile policy toward the DPRK, the article points out, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are now openly talking about international sanctions and formation of siege against the DPRK and concentrating all their efforts on it. Their moves are a deliberate and premeditated provocation to drive the DPRK-Japan hostile relations to a military conflict. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Particularly, their theory of "preemptive attack" on the DPRK is a move as dangerous as a declaration of war to reinvade Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The successive Japanese regimes have enforced their hostile policy toward the DPRK, but they have never openly agitated a war, threatening the sovereignty of the DPRK with the theory of "preemptive attack". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Herein lies the greater danger of Japan's moves for reinvasion of Korea.
 The history of the Japanese imperialists' sanguinary aggression and colonial rule of Korea can neither be forgotten nor be erased no matter how much water may flow under the bridge. Their 40-odd year-long colonial rule was the unheard-of fascist rule to obliterate the soul and resourcefulness of the Korean nation and its five thousand year-long history and cultural tradition and Japanize the whole of Korea. The Korean people are burning with indignation at the crimes of the Japanese imperialists in Korea. The Korean people can never forget the past crimes of Japan no matter how much water may flow under the bridge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is the sworn enemy of the Korean people. It is the firm will of the Korean people to settle accounts with Japan at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We have many things to settle accounts with Japan. The more Japan tries to evade the liquidation of the past crimes and intensifies its moves for reinvasion of Korea, the more the Korean people's hatred for Japan grows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Korean people will wreak their inveterate grudge against Japan in unity under the banner of national cooperation.

61st Anniversary of Liberation of Korea Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate editorials to the 61st anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 Since President Kim Il Sung defeated the brigandish Japanese imperialists and liberated Korea 61 years ago, the Korean nation has come to have its genuine country and greet a new era of enjoying a true life and happiness of humankind for the first time in history, an editorial of Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After its liberation the country has covered the road of proud victory and shining prosperity under the leadership of the President. The country is called Kim Il Sung's Korea and the nation Kim Il Sung's nation as their origin and history of victory and prosperity are unthinkable without his august name and exploits.
 The country liberated and built by the President all his life has fully demonstrated its spirit of powerful prosperity under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the exploits of the President in the construction of the country are great and the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il who has successfully carried forward them is wise, the history of the country is now shining as the history of the President.
 The Songun politics of Kim Jong Il serves as a main guarantee for the dignity of the country shining as a powerful country of independence. His Songun leadership has opened a new heyday in the history of the development of self-defensive military power and single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial refers to the tasks to resolutely defend and eternally glorify the immortal exploits performed by the President in the struggle for the liberation of the country and its prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It calls upon the entire Party, all the army and people to uphold the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il with one mind, devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution and make a fresh leaping progress in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the reunification of the country is the supreme cause of the nation for which the President had worked heart and soul to the last moments of his life, the editorial calls upon all the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and overseas to conduct a vigorous patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself" to resolutely frustrate the U.S. imperialists' new war provocation moves and open a new phase for the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson lays stress on defending the dignity and sovereignty of the nation generation after generation under the banner of Songun.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Performance Given by KPA State Merited Chorus
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il together with servicepersons of the KPA, watched a performance given by the State Merited Chorus of the KPA.
 He was given a standing ovation as he appeared in the auditorium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chorus honored with "Kim Il Sung Order" put on the stage such chorus numbers as "Song Devoted to Marshal Kim Il Sung," "The General Is Banner of Victory", "Song of the Korean People's Army", "My Native Place", "Nobody Knows", "Let Us Meet in Front" and "For the Motherland." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance emotionally sang of the proud path of victory and glory and truthfully portrayed the iron faith and will of the Korean army and people to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche and the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation under the uplifted banner of Songun whatever difficulties and ordeals may stand in their way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance full of revolutionary and militant spirit deeply impressed the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il acknowledged the enthusiastic cheers of performers and audience and congratulated the chorus on its successful performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He extended thanks to the artistes of the chorus, greatly satisfied over their excellent performance fully reflecting the faith and will of the Korean people and the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed great expectation and conviction that all the artistes of the chorus would positively inspire the army and people to fresh struggle and feats with their brisk revolutionary art activities and thus fully demonstrate the might of the chorus as a trumpeter of Songun revolution and a militant art group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA general officers including KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong, first vice department directors of the WPK Central Committee Ri Je Gang and Ri Jae Il and other senior officials of the WPK Central Committee.

Floral Baskets Laid before Kim Il Sung's Statues
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- People from all walks of life across the country laid floral baskets before the statues of President Kim Il Sung today on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of the liberation of the country.
 Pyongyang citizens visited the statue of the President on Mansu Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Standing before the statue was a floral basket sent by   Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army.
 Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music floral baskets in the name of the party and power organs, public organizations, ministries, national institutions, scientific, educational, cultural, art, public health and media organs, factories, enterprises, farms and schools and bouquets and flowers were laid before the statue.
 A floral basket in the name of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front was also presented there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen in the ribbons of the baskets were letters reading "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will live forever", "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will always be with us", "The great revolutionary exploits of the respected leader Generalissimo Kim Il Sung are immortal!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets, bouquets and flowers were also laid before his statues at different units in the city including Kim Il Sung University, the Korean Film Studio and the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people from all walks of life and school youth and children in different parts of the country also placed floral baskets, bouquets and flowers before the statues of Kim Il Sung in their residential quarters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets and bouquets were laid before his statue in Chongjin, North Hamgyong Province, by the consul general and officials of the consulate general of Russia and officials of the consulate general of China and Chinese delegations staying in Chongjin.

Respect Paid to President Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- People from all walks of life visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on August 15 to pay respect to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of the liberation of the country.
 Amid the solemn playing of "Song of General Kim Il Sung", they entered the hall to pay their respects to the statue of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When they entered the hall where the President lies in state, they made a bow to him in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round with deep emotion the Mourning Hall with the portrait of the smiling President and a train which he used during his on-the-spot guidance and visits to foreign countries and a car he used in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation of the Russian Orthodox Church led by its Chairman of the Office for Foreign Relations Kirill, patriarch of Smolensk and Kaliningrad Regions, also visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to the President on the same day.

Wreaths before Liberation Tower and Cemetery of Fallen Fighters of Soviet Army
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- Officials of the Russian embassy here and Russian guests laid wreaths before the Liberation Tower on August 15 on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 The wreath-laying ceremony was attended by Russian Ambassador Andrei Karlov and members of the embassy and a delegation of the Russian Orthodox Church led by its Chairman of the Office for Foreign Relations Kirill, patriarch of Smolensk and Kaliningrad Regions, and a delegation of the Russian Federal State Unitary Enterprise "Cinema Concern 'Mosfilm'" led by its First Deputy General Director Vladimir Ryassov on a visit to the DPRK and diplomatic envoys of different countries here.
 Amid the playing of wreath-laying music wreaths in the name of the Russian embassy and the delegation of the Russian Orthodox Church and bouquets were laid before the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests paid silent tribute to the soldiers of the Soviet Army who fell in the fights to liberate Korea before looking round the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths in the name of the Russian embassy and the delegation of the Russian Orthodox Church and bouquets were also laid before the cemetery of fallen fighters of the Soviet Army in Sadong District, Pyongyang on the same day.

Congratulatory Message to Fidel Castro Ruz
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, together with Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a congratulatory message to Fidel Castro Ruz, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba, president of the Council of State and president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba, on Aug. 13.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We extend most heart-felt congratulations to you on your 80th birthday.
 The Cuban people have honorably defended the dignity and sovereignty of the country and fully demonstrated the advantage and vitality of socialist system in economic, public health, educational and other fields while foiling the U.S. imperialists' moves of aggression, interference and blockade for nearly half a century, which is unthinkable without your revolutionary career. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You embarked upon the road of revolution with your warm love for the country and the people in your early years, ousted the pro-U.S. dictatorial regime for the first time in Latin America through the hard-fought armed struggle and built a genuine people's country in Cuba where they lead a free and new life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are sincerely rejoiced as our own over the achievements made by the fraternal Cuban people in building socialism under your leadership and reconfirm our full support and solidarity to the policy of the Cuban Party and government for defending the motherland, revolution and the gains of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Availing ourselves of this opportunity, we sincerely wish you good health and happiness as well as greater success in your noble work for the prosperity of the country and the promotion of the people's well-being, convinced that the militant ties of friendship forged between our two Parties, two countries and two peoples in the joint struggle for socialism against imperialism would consolidate in the future.
